---
title: Grilled Pear, Gouda & Cheddar Sandwiches with Lemony Arugula & Pecan Salad
description: Upgrade your run-of-the-mill grilled cheese by adding sweet pear and nutty gouda to the mix.  You’ll cook the pear until lightly softened, then layer it onto sourdough slices along with gouda and cheddar. Toast in a buttery pan until golden and melty, and serve with a lemony arugula and pecan salad on the side (all in a quick 20 minutes!).
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/660194aada283ecbc2883bdc-3d3c2e11.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/660194aada283ecbc2883bdc.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/grilled-pear-gouda-and-cheddar-sandwiches-660194aada283ecbc2883bdc
author: Michelle Doll Olson
servings: 2
time required: 20 minutes
cuisine: North America
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 890 kcal
  fat: 61 g
  saturated fat: 26 g
  carbohydrates: 72 g
  sugar: 21 g
  protein: 20 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 1060 mg
---

Wash and dry produce.

Quarter, core, and thinly slice @pear{1%unit}. Halve, peel, and finely chop half the @shallot{1%unit} (whole shallot for 4 servings). Quarter @lemon{1%unit}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} and 1 TBSP @butter{3%tablespoon} in a large pan over medium heat. Add pear, shallot, @honey{2%teaspoon}, juice from one lemon wedge, ½ tsp @sugar{1/2%teaspoon}, and a pinch of @salt{}. Cover and cook, stirring occasionally, until pear has softened, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #small bowl{}. Stir in juice from one lemon wedge (two wedges for 4). Wash out pan.

Evenly layer half the @sourdough bread{4%slices} with @gouda cheese{2%slices} and as much pear as you like. Top with @white cheddar cheese{1/2%cup} and remaining sourdough slices to form sandwiches.

Melt 1 TBSP butter in pan used for pear over medium heat. Once hot, add sandwiches and push around in pan until butter has absorbed. Cook until bread is golden brown and cheese is slightly melted, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> For 4 servings, work in batches or use a second pan, using 1 TBSP butter for each batch.

Add another 1 TBSP butter to pan, then flip sandwiches and push around again until butter has absorbed. Cook until bread is golden brown and cheese is fully melted, ~{4-6%minutes}.

== Lemony Arugula & Pecan Salad ==

While sandwiches are toasting, in a large #bowl{}, whisk together juice from one lemon wedge, 2 TBSP @olive oil{2%tablespoon}, ¼ tsp salt, and @pepper{}. Add @arugula{2%ounce} and @pecans{1/2%ounce}. Toss to thoroughly coat arugula.

> For 4 servings, use juice from two wedges, 4 TBSP olive oil, and ½ tsp salt.

== To Serve ==

Halve sandwiches on a diagonal. Divide sandwiches and salad between plates. Serve.